						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the hundred-pillared <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Viṭhalasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1615 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1438, Dhātu, corresponding to 1615 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records that the hundred-pillared <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> to god Viṭṭhala was caused to be built by the king.</p>						

